# Show Upload Terminal

When running PlatformIO firmware uploads (`pio run -t upload`, `esptool`, or OTA), **always** open the terminal file in the editor so the user can watch the build and upload progress in real time.

## Required Steps

After starting a build/upload command:

1. Use the `open_resource` MCP tool to open the terminal output file in the editor
2. Do this immediately after the command starts — don't wait for it to finish

## Example

```
# 1. Start the upload
Shell: python -m platformio run -e firebeetle32 -t upload

# 2. Immediately open the terminal file so the user can watch
MCP open_resource: file://<terminal_output_file_path>
```

## When This Applies

- Any `platformio run -t upload` command
- Any `esptool` flash or erase command
- Any OTA upload via `espota.py`
- Any long-running build (`platformio run`) without upload
